{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"fields":{"description":"# Finish Jira hard-delete -> outbound re-create (replaces lost epic-3e36)\n\n## Why\nOn a Jira hard-delete the reconciler preserves local content (ADR 0027/0028) BUT never re-creates the Jira\nissue. The path is broken at two joints:\n- **Key mismatch**: `route_inbound_probe` (reconcile.py:316-324, ARCHIVED_OR_MOVED branch) builds the\n  inbound-delete Mutation with `payload={\"reason\": \"hard_delete\", ...}`, but `_apply_inbound_delete`\n  (apply_inbound.py:184) reads `payload.get(\"probe_outcome\", \"out_of_window\")` — so the hard_delete branch is\n  UNREACHABLE (always defaults to out_of_window).\n- **Dropped follow-on**: even when the branch is reached it builds a `follow_on`\n  (apply_inbound.py:202-210, keys `direction/action/target/local_id`, `action=\"create_after_hard_delete\"`, NO\n  `fields`), but the applier consumer (applier.py:467-468) only handles `follow_on.get(\"kind\")==\"suppress_pair\"`\n  — the `create_after_hard_delete` follow-on (which sets `action`, not `kind`) is silently ignored. This is the\n  `epic-3e36` TODO (apply_inbound.py:209-210).\n\n## What (one coherent path: inbound detect -> standard outbound CREATE mutation)\n1. **Canonical key = `reason`.** Change `_apply_inbound_delete` (apply_inbound.py:184) to read\n   `payload.get(\"reason\") or payload.get(\"probe_outcome\", \"out_of_window\")` (accept `reason`, keep back-compat).\n   Update ALL `probe_outcome` fixture sites in `tests/unit/rebar_reconciler/mutate/test_inbound_leaf_bodies.py`\n   — verified there are exactly TWO: line 281 (`payload = {\"probe_outcome\": outcome}`, the parametrized test\n   covering all four outcomes incl. hard_delete) and line 332 (`payload={\"probe_outcome\": \"redirect\", ...}`).\n   Both must carry `reason` (parametrize both keys, or switch to `reason`). (The review's guess of line 289 is\n   stale — no `probe_outcome` there on current main.)\n2. **Reconstruct `fields`.** The follow-on carries `local_id` but not `fields`, and `create_one`\n   (dispatch_one.py:147-156, 168) REQUIRES a `mutation[\"fields\"]`. Fetch the still-present LOCAL ticket by\n   `local_id` and map it via `outbound_fields._map_local_to_jira_fields(ticket, binding_store, ...)`\n   (outbound_fields.py:112-117) — the SAME mapper the outbound differ uses (returns summary/description/\n   issuetype/priority/status/assignee/parent).\n   - **Lookup mechanism (explicit):** the applier inbound loop (applier.py:455-474) has NO `local_tickets` in\n     scope, and there is no by-id helper. `repo_root` IS in scope; read `<repo_root>/.tickets-tracker/<local_id>/\n     .cache.json` `state` directly (single-ticket, cheap), falling back to `reconcile_check.load_local_tickets`\n     only if the cache is absent.\n   - **Failure path:** if the local ticket is absent or `_map_local_to_jira_fields` yields empty/no-summary,\n     do NOT emit a create — log + skip (a hard-deleted ticket with no local content is not re-creatable). Tested.\n3. **Wiring (prior art = the `pending_bug_tickets` side-channel).** Follow the exact pattern applier.py already\n   uses for `pending_bug_tickets` (declared L453, appended L470-474, drained after dispatch): on\n   `follow_on.get(\"action\")==\"create_after_hard_delete\"`, build a STANDARD outbound CREATE `Mutation` (direction\n   outbound, action create, `payload={\"local_id\":…, \"fields\":…}`) and APPEND it to `outbound_list` (applier.py:\n   484-490) BEFORE the `_apply_batch(outbound_list, …)` dispatch (L494-501). No mid-loop `create_one`, no\n   typed-dispatch bypass — it flows through the normal batch -> `create_one` (JQL dedup + `bind_confirm`).\n4. **Idempotency + deferral.** `create_one`'s JQL dedup (`labels = \"rebar-id:<local_id>\"`, dispatch_one.py:\n   194-219) prevents double-create on retry. If `rest_calls >= _REST_CALL_BUDGET` (=200, dispatch_one.py:97,\n   188-192) `create_one` issues zero REST calls, appends to `deferred_creates`, returns None -> the re-create\n   DEFERS to the next pass (same as the normal create path). Test BOTH partial-failure directions:\n   (a) create ok but a following rebind/confirm fails; (b) create deferred by budget exhaustion.\n5. **Stale reverse-index cleanup.** `bind_confirm(local_id, jira_key)` (binding_store.py:276-288) overwrites\n   `bindings[local_id][\"jira_key\"]` and sets `reverse[jira_key]=local_id` but never removes the OLD key's reverse\n   entry (no `rebind` method exists; only `unbind` pops reverse). Fix: at the TOP of `bind_confirm`, read\n   `old_key = entry.get(\"jira_key\")` BEFORE overwriting; if `old_key and old_key != jira_key`, `reverse.pop(old_key,\n   None)` in the SAME save. Edits `binding_store.py`.\n6. **Guard + housekeeping.** Guard the re-create so ONLY a genuine `reason==\"hard_delete\"` triggers it (redirect/\n   out_of_window/trash never re-create). Repoint/remove the `TODO(epic-3e36)` at apply_inbound.py:209-210. Update\n   ADR 0027/0028 to document the now-completed re-create behavior (inbound consumer injects an outbound CREATE\n   into the same pass). Clear the `.joe-janitor/report` flag if present.\n\n## Scope (files)\n- `src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/apply_inbound.py` — key fix + TODO repoint\n- `src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/applier.py` — consume `create_after_hard_delete`, inject outbound CREATE\n- `src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/outbound_fields.py` — import `_map_local_to_jira_fields` (new cross-module\n  coupling: inbound consumer -> outbound field mapper; acceptable, it is the canonical mapper)\n- `src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/binding_store.py` — stale `reverse[old_key]` cleanup in `bind_confirm`\n- `tests/unit/rebar_reconciler/mutate/test_inbound_leaf_bodies.py` — fixture key updates (L281, L332)\n- new tests under `tests/unit/rebar_reconciler/` for the consumer + rebind + failure paths\n- `docs/adr/0027*.md` / `0028*.md` — document completed behavior\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `_apply_inbound_delete` reads `reason` (with `probe_outcome` back-compat); the hard_delete branch is now\n      reachable. Both `probe_outcome` fixture sites (test_inbound_leaf_bodies.py L281, L332) updated; a unit test\n      asserts the hard_delete branch is entered from a `reason`-keyed payload.\n- [ ] The applier consumes `action==\"create_after_hard_delete\"`: it fetches the local ticket by `local_id`,\n      reconstructs `fields` via `_map_local_to_jira_fields`, and appends a standard outbound CREATE Mutation to\n      the pass's `outbound_list` (verified it flows through `create_one`, not a mid-loop bypass).\n- [ ] Consumer failure path: local ticket absent / no mappable summary -> log + skip, no create emitted (tested).\n- [ ] Idempotency + deferral: JQL dedup prevents a double-create on retry; REST-budget exhaustion defers to the\n      next pass. Both partial-failure directions tested (create-ok/rebind-fails; create-deferred).\n- [ ] `bind_confirm` deletes the stale `reverse[old_key]` (read BEFORE overwrite) in the same save; a rebind unit\n      test asserts `reverse` has no dangling old-key entry.\n- [ ] Guard: only `reason==\"hard_delete\"` re-creates (redirect/out_of_window/trash do not) — tested.\n- [ ] Housekeeping: `TODO(epic-3e36)` repointed/removed; ADR 0027/0028 updated to document the completed\n      re-create behavior; `.joe-janitor/report` flag cleared if present.\n- [ ] End-to-end test: a single reconcile pass with an inbound hard-delete probe result produces an outbound\n      CREATE for the still-present local ticket (asserted via the fake acli client's recorded create call),\n      distinct from the unit-level branch/consumer/failure tests above."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783554403869268001,"uuid":"c12f3fd6-f167-4ae4-ae70-4b21bf51d962"}